Heading: II. IT Security Program Standard, Content: 2.17 When confidential data are shared with other institutions, the State, or federal agencies, that shared data should be managed with the security requirements determined to be the highest among the sharing institutions involved and approved by the institutional CIO or data steward (i.e. the member of the institution with responsibility for the data).; Heading: II. IT Security Program Standard, Content: (See NIST Special Publication 800-52 Rev.2 for guidance on encryption of data in transit, and FIPS 140-2 for guidance on encryption of data at rest).; Heading: The Access Control Standard applies to all systems, including those that contain confidential information., Content: 4.4 For systems utilizing authentication, institutions must implement session locking after an institutionally defined period of inactivity and retain the session lock until access is reestablished using established authentication and authorization procedures.
4.5 Users must adhere to institutional password usage, construction, and change requirements. Systems must comply with EITHER (4.5.a or 4.5.b) AND (4.5.c) below:
a. Meet the eAuth guidelines as outlined in 800-63-3B Section 5.1.1.2 Memorized Secret Authenticators;

